-- Hungary Stocks: Mol, Est Media Shares Move in Budapest Trading
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-07-04T15:18:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-04/hungary-stocks-mol-est-media-shares-move-in-budapest-trading.html
The benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index fell 0.4
percent to 17,394.21 by the close in Budapest.  The following were among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Mol Nyrt. (MOL)  ,  Hungary ’s largest refiner, dropped 0.6
percent to 16,600 forint. Brent oil futures retreated from the
highest close in more than a month on speculation that this
week’s gains have been excessive amid concern that a global
economic slowdown may curb demand.  Est Media Vagyonkezelo Nyrt. (ESTMEDIA HB), a Hungarian
entertainment company, fell 14 percent to 32 forint, a record
low. The company offered to sell a stake in Hungary’s biggest
outdoor music festival after failing to attract enough bids for
a bond.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
